<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="137" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,511,1907]" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,562,1123,1150]" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">
Diagnosis (
<figureCitation box="[328,415,1123,1150]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–18" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1960,1985]" captionTargetBox="[194,1404,179,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[169,1419,166,1939]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 15–18. Dorsal, group spondiae: 15. A. alternatus, 16. A. cuernavacensis, 17. A. spondiae, 18. A. vitis. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557877/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">Figs 18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[428,457,1124,1150]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–31" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1692,1717]" captionTargetBox="[171,1413,184,1650]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,174,1673]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 28–31. Head, group spondiae: 28. A. alternatus, 29. A. cuernavacensis, 30. A. spondiae, 31. A. vitis. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557883/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">31</figureCitation>
, 74, 106)
</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schaeffer" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[576,761,1124,1150]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitis">
<emphasis box="[576,761,1124,1150]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">Amblycerus vitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the following combination of characters: eyes distant from each other anteriorly, ocular index: 2.7 (
<figureCitation box="[799,883,1160,1186]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–31" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1692,1717]" captionTargetBox="[171,1413,184,1650]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,174,1673]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 28–31. Head, group spondiae: 28. A. alternatus, 29. A. cuernavacensis, 30. A. spondiae, 31. A. vitis. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557883/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
); ocular sinus 2.6 and postocular lobe 0.2 the eye length; antennae long, going beyond the anterior margin of the hindcoxae; prosternal process longer than anterior coxae and slightly constricted between coxae; scutellum 1.3 longer than wide (Fig. 74); elytra with striae strongly impressed (
<figureCitation box="[280,364,1268,1294]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–18" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1960,1985]" captionTargetBox="[194,1404,179,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[169,1419,166,1939]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 15–18. Dorsal, group spondiae: 15. A. alternatus, 16. A. cuernavacensis, 17. A. spondiae, 18. A. vitis. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557877/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
); at basal third, striae 2–6 with punctures more isolated; all striae free apically; hindtibia lateral spur about 1.2 times the length of median spur; basal tarsomere about 2.5 times the length of the median spur; pygidium without median strip of setae and with moderately coarse and sparse punctures (
<figureCitation box="[1101,1185,1340,1366]" captionStart="FIGURES 84–87" captionStartId="28.[151,264,746,771]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,421,695]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,417,721]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 84–87. Pygidium. group spondiae: 84. A. alternatus, 85. A. cuernavacensis, 86. A. spondiae and 87. A. vitis. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557903/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">Fig. 87</figureCitation>
); median lobe of male genitalia about 4.2 times as long as its greatest width at apical region (
<figureCitation box="[957,1056,1376,1403]" captionStart="FIGURES 103–106" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1589,1614]" captionTargetBox="[251,1338,188,1559]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[238,1349,174,1570]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 103–106. Male genitalia, median lobe, group spondiae: 103. A. alternatus, 104. A. cuernavacensis, 105. A. spondiae and 106. A. vitis. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557911" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557911/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">Fig. 106</figureCitation>
); internal sac in the apical region with a pair of hollow, subtriangular sclerites (
<figureCitation box="[654,751,1412,1439]" captionStart="FIGURES 103–106" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1589,1614]" captionTargetBox="[251,1338,188,1559]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[238,1349,174,1570]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 103–106. Male genitalia, median lobe, group spondiae: 103. A. alternatus, 104. A. cuernavacensis, 105. A. spondiae and 106. A. vitis. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557911" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557911/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">Fig. 106</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schaeffer" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[770,955,1412,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitis">
<emphasis box="[770,955,1412,1438]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">Amblycerus vitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar, in terms of genitalia, to the other three species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kingsolver" authorityYear="1980" box="[374,475,1448,1474]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spondiae">
<emphasis box="[374,475,1448,1474]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">spondiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, from which it differs, however, because it has the apical sclerite subtriangular, non-tuberculate, with straight apex (subtriangular and tuberculate in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[934,1081,1484,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alternatus">
<emphasis box="[934,1081,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">A. alternatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; subquadrate, tuberculate in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuernavacensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">A. cuernavacensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and subtriangular, non-tuberculate and curved apically in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kingsolver" authorityYear="1980" box="[987,1119,1520,1546]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spondiae">
<emphasis box="[987,1119,1520,1546]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">A. spondiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has subtriangular not tuberculate but with acute apex); on the median region, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schaeffer" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[728,807,1556,1582]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitis">
<emphasis box="[728,807,1556,1582]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">A. vitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows a long unpaired wishbone sclerite (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[1291,1437,1556,1582]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alternatus">
<emphasis box="[1291,1437,1556,1582]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">A. alternatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kingsolver" authorityYear="1980" box="[198,330,1592,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spondiae">
<emphasis box="[198,330,1592,1618]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">A. spondiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a short, wishbone and 
<taxonomicName box="[648,852,1592,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuernavacensis">
<emphasis box="[648,852,1592,1618]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="137">A. cuernavacensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a subtrapezoidal sclerite).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
